<span data-type="media" id="fs-idm14049344" data-alt="A Lewis structure is shown. A carbon atom is single bonded to three hydrogen atoms and another carbon atom. The second carbon atom is double bonded to another carbon atom and single bonded to a hydrogen atom. The last carbon is single bonded to two hydrogen atoms.">
<img src="/resources/fbc1bf734d1bf3f3f837ea218cd5d832d608d9d8/CNX_Chem_07_03_Exercise25_img.jpg" data-media-type="image/jpeg" alt="A Lewis structure is shown. A carbon atom is single bonded to three hydrogen atoms and another carbon atom. The second carbon atom is double bonded to another carbon atom and single bonded to a hydrogen atom. The last carbon is single bonded to two hydrogen atoms."/>
